OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, People who take in relatives' children 
OL,6, to keep them out of the care system,   
OL,7, fear having to give them up as living  
OL,8, costs soar, says the charity Kinship.  
OL,10,FIn England and Wales, most kinship     
OL,11,Fcarers get less financial support than 
OL,12,Ffoster carers and some have warned they
OL,13,Fare now struggling, says the charity.  
OL,15,FMinisters say they are working to      
OL,16,Fidentify how best to improve support.  
OL,18,FBut rising prices mean Laura Thornton, 
OL,19,Fwho cares for two half-siblings, gets  
OL,20,F"threatening letters" about her debts. 
